No, it hasn't. Maybe escape worked that way, I don't know.  When feigned you are not invis, but the spell hitting caused the mob that hit you to realize that you are not really dead. They would realize that at quite some distance, not only within aggro range because they can now see you. I don't believe distance effects FD at all.<br>
<br>
I have been nuked numerous times after fading and it never broke the fade. Other mobs in aggro range never reacted. I'm still invised. It has been that way ever since I got fade which was 2 levels and over 400AA ago.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=softlyscreaming>Softly Screaming</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#330000>(6/20/04 10:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19505.topic&index=62>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fade</span><hr size=1> Its happened a few more times, so i'm sure of it now. It isn't breaking invis - I resist most spells that they throw at me anyway.<br>
