&lt;..snip..&gt;<br>
Nothing new here.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
That is not the way it always worked. The nuke does not cause the mob to re-aggro unless this is new with the last patch. I have faded and stood there and taken blasts from a few mobs and then watched them turn around and head home. A concrete example is the two rows of five mobs facing each other in VT, where a good half of them are casters. I dispel one and run down the hall, all ten will aggro. Fade. I've been nuked down two bubs worth standing there. But I'm down the hall and out of aggro range, so they don't notice me. When enough of them have returned to their place in line, I aggro pull by approaching the front mob. If this is changed, I'm dead. My back is already against the wall and the nukes don't all land at once, so I'd have to fade after every blast. <br>
<br>
This behavior is consistent with the definition of what fade does. It removes you from all hate lists and invises. Their nuke hitting does not cause aggro, therefore does not put you on a hate list. If you are too close to a see invis mob, then it may look that way. <br>
<br>
Feign works differently. After a certain level the mob has not really forgotten you. Since it hasn't really forgotten you, a nuke can break a feign. When I used to play a monk I remember watching a mob disappear over the horizon only to come running back after I stood up. It's no wonder monks were given the two minute, you're finally off the hate list reprieve. With a wandering mob they'd have no idea when it was safe to get up. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thommytp>Thommy TP</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#330000>(6/22/04 2:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19505.topic&index=66>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fade</span><hr size=1> The DD in the first Ikkniz trial is now slowable (partially I believe), and warrior using defensive can't keep aggro for $hit. We tried him a couple times, on one of them our wizzy nuked with SoS once, then used clicky pants until he had reduced his aggro as much as he possibly could, and still got summoned /boggle.<br>
